\begin_layout Chapter
Introduction
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\size small
Once you were young.
 No matter how old we may be, all of us were once young.
 We looked at the world through truly fresh eyes, felt it as fully and intensely
 as anyone ever could.
 When we loved, it was the happiest days we had ever known.
 When we were hurt, it was the greatest tragedy we had ever felt.
 And the world shined with possibility.
 We all thought we had a way to change the world, embracing it with all
 our hearts.
 We looked to our heroes and told ourselves "I can do that too".
 It seemed that if only we were given our chance, we could make the world
 better.
 That the pains of the world we felt so strongly were something we could
 overcome...
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\size small
...
 we believed.
 We all once believed.
 And yet, when you look at the world around you today...
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\size small
One day, you saw a man huddling in a corner, covered in all too old rags
 when you came out of the supermarket.
 So many people passed him, looking at him sadly then turning away.
 You could see the desperation on his face.
 You couldn't bear it...
 You give him what cash you had, and a change of clothes.
 It wasn't enough.
 You knew it wasn't enough...
 Not if you were the only one helping.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\size small
That night, you confided in your old friend from kindergarten.
 Who you had always relied on, who had always stood by your side back then.
 ...
 and yet, this time, she frowned.
 She asked you if you really thought that money would really change anything,
 or if he would just use it to buy beer.
 She told you she was worried about how you would live through college if
 you kept doing this.
 She told you that you should let people like that go.
 That night, you cried yourself to sleep.
 Why couldn't you just be like them?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\size small
One day, you told your parents that you wanted to be a writer instead of
 a doctor.
 They told you that you didn't really want that.
 That you wouldn't ever be popular anyway, and you'd be starving on the
 street.
 They told you that if you threw away your life like that, they wouldn't
 help you anymore.
 They told you to stop being stuck in a dream.
 You weren't sure what else you expected...
 everywhere you went, there were so many people who had given up on hoping
 so long ago.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\size small
At least, this time was different.
 That night, you logged into the same chat room you found a few weeks ago.
 One full of people who understand your pains.
 They got it.
 They also still believed.
 They also still dreamed.
 And they comforted you.
 Showed you a way forward.
 Reassured you in the path you chose...
 They told you that it was okay to be you.
 This time, you had less reason to cry.
 Even if you still did.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\size small
One day, you saw a boy crying in the toy aisle, clinging tightly to a stuffed
 animal he wanted.
 But his parents wouldn't have any of that.
 Because boys weren't supposed to like things like that.
 Because boys weren't supposed to cry.
 Because that is not how the world was supposed to be.
 And so many onlookers walked by, even watched with sneers on their faces.
 You couldn't tell who they even were sneering at, the mother or you.
 It didn't matter.
 Nobody helped.
 Nobody else helped.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\size small
...
 but you tried anyway.
 Even as they dragged him away as they called you terrible names.
 He wasn't crying as much anymore.
 ...
 maybe, just maybe.
 You showed him that he wasn't alone in the world.
 Just like your friends once did for you.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\size small
You never could give up, no matter how hard you tried.
 No matter how much everyone around you told you to save yourself, that
 you were naive and only hurting yourself.
 You couldn't stop caring.
 You couldn't stop believing.
 You couldn't stop trying.
 You couldn't forgive yourself if you did.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\size small
And that...
 is what makes you a Luminous.
 Not the shining magic you wield, but the simple fact you could never stop
 dreaming of a better world.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Setting
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Luminous: the Dream is a game about those who dream of a better future inspired
 by the 
\shape italic
mahou shoujo
\shape default
 (or magical girl) genre of Japanese anime and manga.
 It is set in the Chronicles of Darkness, a world much like our own only
 touched by alien wonders and terrors alike.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
...
 this story is not about them.
 It is about humanity, and the one power we can truly call our own.
 Our shining will to change the world.
 A will that blossomed into a force that could only be called magic.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In this game, you play a Luminous, one of the shining souls that wields
 the Light.
 Those like you were hidden, shining dimly through so much of history.
 ...
 but shine they did.
 Writing into the untold margins of history, they built the legacy of light
 you now inherent.
 When you Blossomed, you awoke to the world of dreams they hid deep beyond
 the veil of sleep.
 A dream that reflected the world they wanted to wake up to some day, and
 that would shape the Light you would use to bring that world about.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It will not be easy.
 The world has been a dark place from the start, and even now that clouds
 humanity's hearts.
 There were always those who wouldn't or couldn't dream of brighter.
 Those who merely wished to survive, those who had the hope beaten out of
 them by their parents, those who did not want to make the world better,
 only end up on top.
 They too, have the will to change the world.
 The Luminous call that reversed mirror of their own power the Darkness.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
At least.
 This time...
 glimmers of light finally shine through that long and dark night.
 Over the generations, we have created so many wonders.
 We had solved so many of our problems.
 The internet now connects those of the Light together in a way they had
 never had before.
 Medicine lessens so many of the pointless tragedies of the past.
 And so much more...
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Perhaps the tide is turning.
 Perhaps this time, dawn will come.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Themes
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
While it could be used to tell many kinds of stories, in the end Luminous:
 the Dream is about the contrast between dreams and idealism vs the harshness
 of realities and the necessities of survival.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
Distant Dreams
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
You dream of a better world, and you know how you could help the world get
 there.
 But it's still not easy.
 A Luminous can defeat the monster, she can win the election and start instituti
ng reforms, she can rescue the cute boy.
 But in the end, a single person can still only do so much even with magic.
 The dream of the Luminous can only be achieved together, when a hundred
 million small victories add up.
 It isn't easy.
 It is a struggle.
 But it is worth it in the end.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
Distant Legacies
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Light and Darkness, the human hopes and fears they reflect were all
 passed down down the generations.
 All those who live today are heir to that heritage, and the wielders of
 humankind's Will are no exception.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
A Turning Point
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Perhaps, for the first time in history, something can be done.
 Even as the technologies and ideas that have made the world better have
 entrenched the fears and greed of those in power...
 it too empowers those who hope.
 For the first time, those like you are able to come together in a way you
 never had been able to before.
 Maybe.
 Just maybe.
 This time, the Light will win rather than simply shining in the background
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Media
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
Magia Record: Puella Magi Madoka Magica Side Story
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A different story from the popular original, Magia Record’s focus pivoted
 more to the human response to the woes of magic in a dark world.
 It focuses on relationships, girls pulling each other from the brink of
 despair, and standing up for what’s right.
 With many side-stories in the original phone game, it showcased slice-of-life
 episodes that brought attention to the bonds needed to survive being a
 magical girl.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
Senki Zesshou Symphogear
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
While more seinen than most conventional magical girl shows, Symphogear
 is underlined with themes of heartfelt communication between people who
 otherwise misunderstand each other, determination to protect, and what
 we sacrifice in order to protect.
 The main character, Hibiki, embodies much of what the Luminous stand for,
 with her belief in the ability to reach to the heart, and the refusal to
 give up in the heart of darkness, whether it be in actual battle or peoples
 own despair.
 Each member of the main cast suffers tragedy, and it’s through their bonds
 with others that they’re able to stand up again.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
The Lego Movie 2: The Second Part
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Whereas the first movie focused on creativity and freedom, the second discusses
 true maturity.
 It shows that growing up doesn’t mean that the things you believed in when
 younger have to be forgotten and let go of.
 It tells of how even in a darker world, hoping is not in vain.
 The movie shows the world like the Luminous see it; almost everyone else
 loses their flame, their light, their hope in the world, because they believe
 it’s the only way to survive.
 But it isn't true.
 The song Everything’s Not Awesome summarizes it all fairly well.
 
\end_layout

