\begin_layout Section
Dreamer's Heart
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Far too often, Luminous find themselves wanting to change the world when
 they personally experience the cruelties of the world.
 They cannot help but feel the pains of those around them, and even if they
 escape the worst of it personally, they almost certainly grow close to
 someone who suffers from it for one reason or another.
 They are themselves hurt by a world that tells them they are naive to hope,
 and a thousand times again when they see the pain reflected in another.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Mundane and Supernatural Aspirations
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Hopeful are caught between the mundane and the supernatural, and their
 goals reflect that.
 They balance between the strains of everyday life, and the hidden problems
 of the supernatural world that exists on the margins of society.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Luminous have five Aspirations instead of the usual three.
 Two of them must relate to her personal life or the broader mundane world,
 and two of them must relate to the supernatural world.
 The last Aspiration may be assigned freely.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Sensitivity A Luminous' strong emotions combined with their natural concern
 for others meld together into a deep empathy they call "Sensitivity", only
 growing stronger from their magic to connect hearts.
 Sensitivity is a dice pool equal to half the Hopeful's Reverie rounded
 up.
 Merits and other abilities may add additional dice to this pool, and non-Lumino
us may gain Sensitivity dice through merits or other traits.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Take their Hand 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As much as the pains of others hurt them too, the Luminous can at least
 put it to good use.
 The level of connection they can have makes it easier for them to comfort
 and understand others.
 Sensitivity provides the following bonuses:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
You add your Sensitivity as a bonus to mundane Empathy or any Resonate rolls
 to understand how someone feels, comfort them, or assure them of their
 own worth and value.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
You may attempt to comfort someone facing a breaking point, reassuring them
 that at the very least, they are not alone.
 Roll Presence + Sensitivity.
 Take Hope damage equal to your number of successes, and add that many dice
 as a bonus to your target's roll.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
When you act as a Touchstone to another character with a Hope track or similar
 mechanic, you may add your Sensitivity to the amount of Hope damage healed.
 A character can benefit from this extra healing only once a day.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Reflected Wounds
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A Luminous fuels her power with the strength of her emotions, and far too
 often, the weight of the world can turn it back onto her.
 She cannot help but feel an echo of the emotional pain those who are suffering
 feels, even as she does her best to help those around her.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Whenever a Hopeful witnesses or learns about a situation that caused someone
 significant emotional pain, she takes a mild Hope attack with dice equal
 to her Sensitivity.
 Deliberate acts of cruelty add a dice to this attack, and particularly
 heinous acts (such as prolonged deliberate torture) may add up to three
 dice or instead cause severe Hope damage.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Afterwards, she may immediately replace a short-term aspiration with one
 to alleviate the pain, or prevent the one who caused it from doing so again.
 When she completes such an Aspiration, she gains an additional beat and
 recovers all mild Hope damage.
 Luminous may have no more than two aspirations from Sensitivity at once.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Hope 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When a Luminous first Blossoms, she becomes the dreams and wonders she always
 knew as a child.
 She reclaims the emotion and imagination that she once knew, feeling her
 triumphs and struggles as strongly as she did the first time she truly
 opened her eyes to the world.
 The challenges of life and the shadows of the world around her hurt her
 so deeply.
 But...
 she can always turn to the wonders remaining in the world.
 Cling to them for strength, bouncing back than any normal person could
 ever hope to.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Luminous have Hope instead of Integrity, a measurement of her emotional
 well being and will to fight.
 When her Hope is damaged, she feels down and drained, and the conviction
 to continue her work starts slipping away.
 At more severe Hope damage, she begins feeling outright helpless in the
 face of the world's darkness.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*
Hope Track 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Luminous have a Hope track equal to their transformed Power + Resistance
 that behaves similarly to a health track.
 When an ability refers to a character's Hope, it means the number of undamaged
 Hope boxes she possesses.
 Luminous are considered to have an Integrity equivalent equal to 5 + her
 undamaged Hope boxes (to a maximum of 10).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*
Hope Damage and Recovery 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Events that shake a Hopeful's resolve or strain her emotions cause her to
 suffer an attack against her Hope.
 She may take two kinds of Hope damage as a result.
 Mild Hope damage represents simpler emotional strain from her overexerting
 her magic or simply the weight of life bearing down on her without a release.
 Severe Hope damage represents fundamentally deeper pains that linger, even
 when the situation clears up.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Each time a Luminous takes Hope damage, mark it off her Hope track using
 a slash (/) for mild damage and an (X) for severe damage.
 Mark mild damage in the leftmost empty box of her Hope track, and severe
 damage in the leftmost empty box or the leftmost box that is marked with
 only mild damage.
 Whenever a Princess takes mild Hope damage when her rightmost Hope box
 is filled, she instead takes a point of severe Hope damage.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Once a day, whenever she spends time relaxing or otherwise doing something
 she enjoys without expectation or consequences for failure, roll Hope.
 She clears a box of mild Hope damage equal to her successes.
 If one or more of your Touchstones joined her in the activity, she heals
 an additional box of mild Hope damage, or reduces a box of severe damage
 to mild damage.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*
Attacks against Hope
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When something shakes a Princess' resolve or emotional stability, they take
 an attack against Hope.
 Attacks can be mild or severe and have a dice rating.
 Roll a dice pool equal to the die rating of the attack.
 The Luminous takes a number of the stated severity of Hope damage equal
 to the corresponding to the number of successes.
\end_layout

