\begin_layout Standard
The Hopeful draw deeply on their own dreams to power their magic, and forces
 that try to alter it do not easily escape their notice.
 A Luminous is always aware of any attempts to use supernatural powers or
 other extraordinary means to influence, alter or read any aspect of her
 mind, and reflexively resists them.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
She gains a bonus equal to her Hope to contested rolls against such effects.
 Non-contested rolls against her suffer a penalty equal to her Hope, even
 if they do not normally allow resistance.
 If she has no damaged Hope boxes, she additionally adds an automatic success
 to such contested rolls, and non-contested rolls against her subtract one
 success from the result.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Echo 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A Dreamer's magic touches the heart of everyone they treasure and love dearly,
 connecting their dreams together in their deepest sleep.
 Over time, those close to the Luminous come to understand each other on
 a level that goes beyond simple words.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Echos function in both Mundane Form and Dream Form.
 Their influence is typically subtle and hard to notice, however, and only
 affects those already close to the Luminous.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Intimacy 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Dream is woven out of the countless bonds and ties that connect people,
 interweaving all of humanity together into a single tapestry.
 The strength of the connection between two given people is called Intimacy.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Connected:
\series default
 The two people are so close that the distinction between them does not
 matter, often being bound by magical vows and ties.
 This usually applies to extremely close lovers, platonic life partners,
 and those bound by vows such as those between a Changeling and the Avowed
 or the Weave of Bonds 
