\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Strong:
\series default
 The two people are very close to each other, often sharing much of their
 lives with each other and confiding in each other for comfort and support.
 This often applies to those such as typical married couples, very close
 friends, parents and their children, or family of choice.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Medium:
\series default
 The two people are on friendly terms with each other and come to know each
 other on deeper terms.
 This often applies to those such as good friends, confidants, siblings,
 or a typical dating couple.
 Weak: The two people have met each other before, and interact on occasion
 but rarely in particular depth.
 This often applies to those such as coworkers, gaming partners, extended
 family, or a friend of a friend.
 Hostile or unfriendly relationships also fall under this category, though
 some kinds of ambiguous relationships (such as a passionate rivalry) can
 justify stronger Intimacy.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Described:
\series default
 You have a basic idea of who the person is, but have not interacted directly
 in any significant manner.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
These bonds must be mutual and cannot be strained by formal contexts or
 ingenious premises.
 If two people have different feelings towards each other, the lower Intimacy
 implied holds.
 For example, a therapist and her patient often only have Weak Intimacy,
 despite how much of her patient's life she learns, as they only interact
 in formal contexts, and are effectively forbidden from having a relationship
 beyond a very formal and professional one.
 Similarly, unrequited love from a stalker rarely produces more than Weak
 Intimacy unless reciprocated.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Sometimes, Intimacy is used as a penalty to the dice pool of abilities.
 When it is used in this way, Connected Intimacy provides no penalty, Strong
 Intimacy inflicts a -2 penalty, Medium intimacy provides a -4 penalty,
 Weak Intimacy inflicts a -8 penalty, and Described Intimacy inflicts a
 -12 penalty.
 When using such an ability, you may use the Intimacy of a person you are
 touching, at the cost of decreasing the Intimacy by one level.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Read the Winds
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Luminous are innately aware of the general feeling and mood of any location
 they enter through their Echo.
 This does not depend on its present occupants, but rather the impression
 those who frequent the zone leave on the Dream, especially those with the
 strongest emotions.
 While this never directly triggers Sensitivity, it can make Hope recovery
 or even simply relaxing in a place next to impossible.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Interwoven Dreams 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Luminous and those who are close to each other dream of each other, and
 with each other, linked by the overlapping Echos of those involved.
 A Luminous' Echo influences the dreams of those with strong Intimacy with
 her, and their dreams in turn influence her back.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Luminous share their dreams they have Connected Intimacy with.
 In their dreams, they face the same challenges and see the same wonders
 side by side, perspective sometimes blurring between the two in the Dream's
 depths.
 They come to know each other's depths through those half-remembered dreams.
 Luminous and those with Connected ties to them gain an automatic success
 on all mundane skill rolls to understand or emphasize with each other.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Luminous and those they have Strong Intimacy with often dream of each other,
 sometimes sharing their dreams entirely.
 They gain the rote quality on all mundane skill rolls to understand or
 emphasize with each other.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Luminous and those with Medium Intimacy dream of each other in vague terms,
 catching glimpses of each other's depths they would not otherwise see in
 their waking lives.
 They gain 9-Again on mundane skill rolls to understand or emphasize with
 each other.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Lesser degrees of Intimacy are not strong enough to have any effect.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This effect applies separately to a Hopeful's Mundane and Dream forms, and
 these dreams do not penetrate the protection of Dual Identity at Strong
 Intimacy or weaker.
 However, the dreams of those with Connected Intimacy will almost certainly
 breach those protections by nature.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Reflected Light 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Even in their waking life, a Luminous' Echo allows her and those closer
 to her to draw on each other for strength.
 Once per scene, either may spend a Willpower to reflect a Virtue, Dream,
 Wish or similar Anchor of someone they have Strong or closer Intimacy with
 until the scene ends.
 This grants 9-Again for all actions that follow that Anchor.
 In addition, Luminous gain the Anchor for all purposes including Willpower
 recovery.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Flaring an Echo 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A Luminous may flare her Echo as an instant action at any time, or as an
 reflexive action while transforming by spending two Willpower.
 She focuses on the emotion and meanings underlying her Dream, and projects
 it forth through her Echo.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
An Echo intensified in this way conveys her Dream and inner truths to everyone
 who sees her, not only those with preexisting ties to her.
 She rolls Reverie + Hope.
 If she succeeds, she inflicts the Echo Flare tilt on everyone within the
 general vicinity, granting them 9-again on all actions that align with
 her Dream and causing actions antithetical to her Dream to lose 10-again.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Someone affected by Echo Flare may shake it off by spending a Willpower
 reflexively and rolling Composure + Resolve.
 If she gains an equal number or more successes than the Luminous' roll,
 she loses the tilt.
 The tilt otherwise naturally ends at the scene's end.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Luminous may contest an Echo Flare with her own Echo, contesting it with
 Reverie + Hope.
 If she wins, she is not affected by the aura, and instead inflicts her
 own Echo Flare against the other Luminous.
 Many other types of supernatural beings have innate auras that inflict
 Conditions or Tilts.
 Luminous may contest their active flares with her Echo as well, in the
 same way as Echos.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Transformation 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The mundane world rejects magic, so strongly so that to be openly something
 else is simply a death sentence.
 The Hopeful, as always, adapted to their circumstances.
 Torn between the mundane world they so desperately wish to be better, and
 the supernatural world they are inevitably a part of, they choose to be
 both, splitting their two lives across their forms.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In their mundane form, they are truly mundane with only the barest wisps
 of their magic, and all the vulnerability that entails.
 In their Dream Form, the Luminous become a living dream, taking on the
 form they do in their most fond fantasies.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Luminous may switch between their two forms at will, with a transformation
 action.
 Transformation normally takes an instant action.
 Transforming reflexively requires spending a Willpower.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Mundane Form 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In their mundane form, the Hopeful do not simply wear a mask of normal humanity.
 Rather, they are simply normal humans as they've always been.
 Their magic is sealed away in their own heart, as simply another seemingly
 mundane fantasy.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
All supernatural effects treat a Luminous in Mundane Form as if she were
 a normal mortal, whether this is beneficial or harmful to her.
 She may transform reflexively to better resist such abilities.
 Abilities that would cause a Luminous to become another type of supernatural
 being or otherwise cease to be a Luminous still always fail, even if they
 would otherwise work on mortals.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
However, she loses access to the majority of her supernatural powers.
 A Luminous in her Mundane Form has no Wisp Capacity, and loses access to
 her Regalia, Domains and Charms.
 She still retains her Supernatural Tolerance, but only for purposes of
 resisting or contesting supernatural abilities.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Dream Form 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Hopeful dream vividly and brightly, taking on a form reflecting their
 deepest wishes, freed from the constraints of reality.
 In their waking life, they call upon an innate magic to project that form
 into reality.
 For some, they become just themselves in a different outfit.
 Others become fantastical beings of all sorts – winged fairies, catgirls,
 masked heroes, paladins in shining armor.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In this form, they greet the hidden corners of the world, matching the power
 of its other denizens with their own shining dreams.
 In this form, all too often, they seek an escape from the pressures of
 mundane life.
 They mingle with the stranger creatures of the night, or join the parties
 of the Kindred or Architects.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Luminous in their Dream Form are ephemeral beings in phase with astral projectio
ns, Goetia, and other similar dream entities.
 They have a Rank equal to half their Reverie (rounded up), are always Materiali
