\begin_layout Subsection
Dream Health 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A Hopeful's Dream Form is composed of dreamstuff instead of flesh and blood,
 protecting her material forms from harm.
 She has a separate health track in Dream Form called Dream Health, with
 boxes equal to her Resistance + transformed attribute cap.
 It behaves like a normal health track for all purposes.
 Damage she takes in her Dream Form never carries over to her mundane form,
 and furthermore, she may transform reflexively in response to damage or
 any other source of harm.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Regardless of whether she is currently in her Dream Form, she recovers all
 damage to her Dream Health after a restful night's sleep when she would
 recover Willpower.
 Furthermore, every 15 minutes out of combat, she recovers one box of bashing
 damage or reduces a box of lethal damage to bashing damage.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As with all ephemeral beings, physical attacks against a Luminous in Dream
 Form do bashing damage instead of lethal damage.
 Whenever she takes a box of aggravated damage, she also suffers a box of
 mild Hope damage.
 Furthermore, she applies Defense to all attacks including firearms.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Luminous never suffer wound penalties when transformed.
 Should the rightmost box of her Dream Health be filled with lethal or aggravate
d damage, she immediately reverts to her Mundane Form and gains the Soul
 Shocked condition.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Transformed Attributes 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In a dream, when you break down a metal door, it doesn't matter how strong
 you are -- only your determination to have it out of the way.
 When you convince your lover to stay by your side, it's not the words that
 matter, but the feeling you already hold.
 When you fix a computer dropped into a lake, it's not really how much you
 know about computers, but rather how well you can convince your dream that
 you can.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Luminous in their Dream Forms interact with the world in the same surreal
 ways, drawing on the collective knowledge of the Dream and their own imaginatio
n to interact with the world.
 Even the smallest things they do are touched by this power.
 Thus, they use the simplified three Attributes of ephemeral entities.
 Each transformed attribute is equal to the highest of the Luminous' three
 corresponding mundane attributes.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Power describes the Luminous' ability to impose upon the world through force
 of will, intellectual prowess or personality.
 It equals the highest of Strength, Intelligence, and Presence.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Finesse describes how well the Luminous can affect the world through great
 skill or subtle manipulation.
 It equals the highest of Dexterity, Wits, and Manipulation.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Resistance describes how well the Luminous can withstand the will and manipulati
on of others.
 It equals the highest of Constitution, Resolve, and Composure.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
She uses these attributes in place of each corresponding mundane attribute.
 If this would cause a roll to use the same attribute twice, the roll is
 slightly modified.
 Resistance + Resistance is instead rolled as Resistance + Finesse.
 Finesse + Finesse is instead rolled as Power + Finesse.
 Power + Power is instead rolled as Power + Resistance.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Transformed Skills
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Unlike most ephemeral beings, Luminous have a reduced set of eight skills
 instead of lacking skills.
 Like their transformed attributes, each transformed skill is the highest
 of three of their mundane skills reflecting a way of approaching and solving
 problems more than specific fields of knowledge.
 When a supernatural power or other mechanic calls for a specific skill,
 use the combined skill in place of its component skills.
 In cases where an action would fall under a different transformed skill
 than the one corresponding to the relevant mundane skill, use the more
 appropriate transformed skill.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*
Force
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Force Skill describes a Luminous' raw physical strength and raw magical
 power.
 It is used for actions like hand-to-hand combat, wielding weapons, direct
 and forceful magical assaults, intimidating another through force of will,
 or displays of strength.
 In combat, this is the skill used to make grapples and attack with mundane
 melee or thrown weapons.
\series bold

\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

Sample Actions:
\series default
 Breaking boards (Power + Force), Stare down (Power + Force), Take a blow
 (Resistance + Force)
\series bold

\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

Component Skills:
\series default
 Brawl, Weaponry, and Intimidation
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*
Flow 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Flow Skill describes the Luminous' ability to move gracefully or precisely
 and control themselves at high speeds.
 It is used for actions like dancing, jumping between a building's rooftops,
 climbing a roof, driving a car in stressful situations or playing sports.
 In combat, Flow is used to defend against attacks and attack with mundane
 ranged weapons.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\series bold
Sample Actions:
\series default
 Dance performance (Finesse + Flow), Drive Vehicles (Finesse + Flow), Climb
 a wall (Power + Flow) 
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\series bold
Component Skills:
\series default
 Athletics, Drive, Firearm
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*
Learn 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Learn Skill describes the Luminous' general knowledge and ability to
 learn new things.
 It is used to research a topic, perform web searches, perform scientific
 experiments, investigate a crime scene or recall general knowledge about
 fields such as geography or basic maths and sciences.
 It does not cover specialized or higher level knowledge.
 Such actions use the Lore skill instead.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\series bold
Sample Actions: 
\series default
Perform an internet search (Finesse + Learn), Recall historical facts (Power
 + Learn), Examine a crime scene (Finesse + Learn) 
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\series bold
Component Skills: 
\series default
Academics, Investigate, Survival
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*
Lore
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Lore Skill describes the Luminous' knowledge of specific technical topics
 and mechanics of the world.
 It is used to diagnose and treat illnesses and injuries, hack computer
 systems, identify animal tracks, or identify the species of a tree.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\series bold

\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

Sample Actions: 
\series default
Hack a computer (Power + Lore), Gather facts into a theory (Power + Lore),
